1
00:00:11,208 --> 00:00:13,125
[YUU]
Thanks. Well, goodnight, then.

2
00:00:39,791 --> 00:00:40,791
[YUU grunts]

3
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:51,416
All right. I sent him away.

4
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,208
Thanks, Mom. I'm sorry.

5
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:56,375
Are you sure it's
what you want?

6
00:00:57,541 --> 00:00:58,958
Yeah.

7
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:01,250
Yeah. I am sure.

8
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:12,500
♪

9
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:25,041
<i>The place that I always dreamed</i>

10
00:01:25,125 --> 00:01:28,000
<i>I'd reach one day</i>
<i>is too high above us</i>

11
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:29,083
<i>To get to</i>

12
00:01:29,166 --> 00:01:31,250
<i>The promise we made is fading</i>

13
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:34,375
<i>every moment we</i>
<i>conform like they do</i>

14
00:01:34,458 --> 00:01:35,750
<i>I wanna move on my own</i>

15
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,125
<i>Step away from the crowd</i>

16
00:01:37,208 --> 00:01:38,583
<i>I wanna dance to my own beat</i>

17
00:01:38,666 --> 00:01:40,958
<i>I'm done trying to blend in</i>

18
00:01:42,166 --> 00:01:44,750
<i>I won't be tied</i>
<i>to a tedious world</i>

19
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:47,583
<i>Repeating each day like</i>
<i>a broken record sickens me</i>

20
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:50,125
<i>(No matter how I try</i>
<i>I can't escape repetition)</i>

21
00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:51,291
<i>It's hard to change it up</i>

22
00:01:51,375 --> 00:01:52,875
<i>When no one else is listening</i>

23
00:01:52,958 --> 00:01:54,666
<i>We're in a box, stuck in a box</i>

24
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:57,208
<i>Meant to stifle what we feel</i>

25
00:01:57,291 --> 00:01:59,958
<i>Forced to erase all</i>
<i>that we know is real</i>

26
00:02:00,041 --> 00:02:01,208
<i>But I refuse to be locked up</i>

27
00:02:01,291 --> 00:02:02,291
<i>Won't live in this prison</i>

28
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:04,208
<i>Gotta fight for open skies</i>

29
00:02:05,416 --> 00:02:07,000
<i>Time to break free</i>

30
00:02:07,083 --> 00:02:10,958
<i>Open our hearts to a world and</i>
<i>go racing forward to the light</i>

31
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,666
<i>These broken chains</i>
<i>can't hold us back</i>

32
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:16,666
<i>We're finally on track to heal</i>
<i>all the fractures in ourselves</i>

33
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:18,041
<i>As we climb and ascend</i>

34
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:19,375
<i>Aiming high to the end</i>

35
00:02:19,458 --> 00:02:21,833
<i>We'll feel a climber's high</i>

36
00:02:21,916 --> 00:02:24,666
<i>Hear these words and know your</i>
<i>dream can be stronger than steel</i>

37
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,875
<i>Just believe</i>

38
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:26,666
<i>You have the power</i>

39
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:30,291
<i>Let your voice be heard</i>

40
00:02:30,375 --> 00:02:35,375
♪

41
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:40,375
[rock music plays]


42
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,875
[sighs] Welp, I guess
that'll work.

43
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:00,750
[MIKASA] Come on,
it's better than passable.

44
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:02,291
Yuu's song turned
out great, man.

45
00:03:02,375 --> 00:03:04,708
Nachi, you really need
to watch those rhythms.

46
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:06,458
You got way off
a couple of times.

47
00:03:06,541 --> 00:03:07,958
Yeah, I know.

48
00:03:08,041 --> 00:03:09,833
Sometimes I get carried away
when I'm really feelin' it.

49
00:03:09,916 --> 00:03:11,833
I kinda dig your
passionate side.

50
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:13,583
I find it very attractive.

51
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,375
Ugh! Cut it out!

52
00:03:15,458 --> 00:03:18,416
[MIKASA chuckles]

53
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,541
[NACHI]
You're being super creepy.

54
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:21,916
Stop laughing!

55
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,333
Hey, so, listen--we need
to talk about something.

56
00:03:24,416 --> 00:03:25,625
Uh?

57
00:03:25,708 --> 00:03:27,375
My brother got a call.

58
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:30,583
It was from that same club
where we played the last time.

59
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:32,875
They want us to come play again.

60
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,875
What do you think?
Can we do it?

61
00:03:36,958 --> 00:03:39,583
Wow. Look, I don't know, man.

62
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:48,333
[YUU]
I'll go find Akitsuki.

63
00:03:48,416 --> 00:03:52,083
And I'll convince her
to change her mind.

64
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:53,416
Are you sure?

65
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,583
Yes.

66
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:56,708
She'll come back.

67
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:59,083
All right! Let's do it, then!

68
00:03:59,166 --> 00:04:00,833
Sounds great to me.

69
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:02,041
Okay.

70
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:04,291
I'll tell my brother
that we're good to go.

71
00:04:04,375 --> 00:04:05,833
We will be!

72
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:09,208
[beep]

73
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:10,708
[YUU]
Hey, it's me.

74
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,333
Sorry to keep calling.

75
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:15,125
But I really need
to talk to you.

76
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:16,583
Um. See...

77
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:19,416
We have a gig coming up,
two weeks from Saturday.

78
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,958
Please, Akitsuki,

79
00:04:21,041 --> 00:04:22,583
can I see you just once?

80
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:23,708
Everybody misses you--

81
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:24,875
[beep]

82
00:04:27,625 --> 00:04:29,541
Was that Haruna?

83
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:31,583
[FUUKA]
Yeah.

84
00:04:31,666 --> 00:04:34,250
I mean, I've already
told him I'm going solo.

85
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:36,083
What a weirdo!

86
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:50,041
[FUUKA]
I can't go back.

87
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:52,208
I can't be around him.

88
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:54,333
It's too hard.

89
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,958
[dishes clinking]

90
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:03,875
[door clicks]

91
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:06,666
[door slams]

92
00:05:14,541 --> 00:05:17,291
[FUUKA gasps]

93
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:18,791
Oh, thank you!

94
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:20,583
I'm a total klutz.

95
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:23,583
Uh! Koyuki?

96
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:30,833
[KOYUKI] I know it can be
really tough at first

97
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:32,958
because everything
is so new for you.

98
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,875
It was the same for me.

99
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:39,833
Just remember:

100
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:42,375
you're getting to
live your dream.

101
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:43,666
Yeah.

102
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:52,041
Hey, listen.

103
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:53,833
You should know,

104
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:56,125
I've ended things
between Nico and me.

105
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:57,291
[gasps]

106
00:05:58,041 --> 00:05:59,041
It's funny.

107
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:01,875
I can't even remember
not loving him.

108
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:04,958
I've loved him my whole
life without trying.

109
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:08,375
But I think, maybe that's
why I couldn't see it--

110
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:10,416
what he was really feeling.

111
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:15,375
At your gig,
I listened to your song.

112
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,125
The lyrics were pretty clear.

113
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:18,500
[FUUKA]
Huh?

114
00:06:18,583 --> 00:06:20,416
[KOYUKI]
I don't know if you remember,

115
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,250
but you told me once before
that you'd never given much

116
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,500
thought to falling in love.

117
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,458
[KOYUKI] But the feeling
behind "For You"

118
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,416
really resonated with me.

119
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,625
I recognized it.

120
00:06:32,708 --> 00:06:34,208
What?! It's just a song!

121
00:06:34,291 --> 00:06:36,166
I thought about what it would
feel like to have a one-sided

122
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:37,375
crush and I wrote about it!

123
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:40,458
I've got a stellar
imagination, that's all!

124
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,791
Look, Fuuka.

125
00:06:42,875 --> 00:06:45,166
I think it's time you were
honest with yourself.

126
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:47,125
[FUUKA]

127
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:50,500
Once you are, things
will get a lot easier.

128
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:52,541
I can promise you that.

129
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,375
I was hoping I'd get a chance
to say this stuff to you.

130
00:06:57,458 --> 00:07:00,166
So, good we ran into each other.

131
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:03,208
[KOYUKI]
See ya 'round.

132
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,500
Okay, I'm takin' off.

133
00:07:18,583 --> 00:07:20,541
'Kay. Good work.

134
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,916
He heading to Fuuka's house?

135
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,041
Yeah.

136
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:30,500
He's been going by
her place this week,

137
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:33,000
every night after practice,
but she hasn't been there,

138
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:36,708
and I haven't seen
her at school, either.

139
00:07:36,791 --> 00:07:38,541
[NACHI]
Hey, do you think it would help

140
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:39,875
if we all went over there?

141
00:07:39,958 --> 00:07:40,916
Nah.

142
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,958
Yuu needs to handle
this on his own.

143
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:46,833
But I know something the three
of us can do in the meantime.

144
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,125
[NACHI]
Huh?

145
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:54,125
Practice up!

146
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:56,416
So, when she finally decides
to come back, she'll wonder

147
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:59,291
why she ever left
in the first place!

148
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:01,833
Yeah! I'm so down!

149
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:04,250
[SUZUKA]
I'm sorry.

150
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,291
I'm afraid she isn't home yet.

151
00:08:06,375 --> 00:08:09,166
Oh, no worries. Sorry I'm
always dropping by.

152
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:11,208
I feel awful that you
keep missing her.

153
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:14,208
It's okay. I'll come again.

154
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:16,500
Wait! Just one more thing!

155
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:42,500
Look, Fuuka. I think it's time
you were honest with yourself.

156
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,458
[FUUKA]
I'm home.

157
00:08:57,875 --> 00:08:59,500
[FUUKA]
You guys might know this one.

158
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,583
Here's "Climber's High"
by the Hedgehogs.

159
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:02,833
[CROWD cheering]

160
00:09:02,916 --> 00:09:04,541
[drum sticks tapping]

161
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:05,500
[SUZUKA]
Fuuka!

162
00:09:05,583 --> 00:09:06,875
How was your night?

163
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:08,291
[rock music plays]

164
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:09,625
[FUUKA]
What are you watching?

165
00:09:09,708 --> 00:09:12,208
Sorry, I thought you'd
be home late, so...

166
00:09:12,291 --> 00:09:13,416
It's cool.

167
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,125
[FUUKA] ♪ The place that I
always dreamed ♪

168
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:25,125
♪ I'd reach one day is
too high above us ♪

169
00:09:25,208 --> 00:09:26,041
♪ To get to... ♪

170
00:09:26,125 --> 00:09:28,083
[SUZUKA]
You all look so happy.

171
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:31,541
You have the biggest
smile on your face.

172
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:33,041
Are you happy now?

173
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:36,083
Like, are you still doing
what you love, honey?

174
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,750
I just mean, it's
been a long time

175
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:40,000
since I've seen you
smile like that.

176
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:42,333
♪ I won't be tied
to a tedious world ♪

177
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:43,916
♪ Repeating each day like
a broken record... ♪

178
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,583
I remember being your age.

179
00:09:45,666 --> 00:09:48,208
Things were really
overwhelming and confusing.

180
00:09:48,291 --> 00:09:50,750
Sometimes, it seemed
like too much.

181
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:52,250
But you know,

182
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:55,166
I think the most important
thing is not being afraid to be

183
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:57,791
true to who you really are.

184
00:09:57,875 --> 00:09:59,208
Well, there you go.

185
00:09:59,291 --> 00:10:02,791
Advice from your wise,
old mom, take it or leave it.

186
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:08,041
I just know it's hard when you
leave things unresolved.

187
00:10:08,125 --> 00:10:10,666
Here. Haruna left this.

188
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:13,750
♪ ...on track to heal all
the fractures in ourselves ♪

189
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:15,208
♪ As we climb and ascend ♪

190
00:10:15,291 --> 00:10:19,125
♪ Aiming high to the end
We'll feel a climber's high ♪

191
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:42,000
[YUU]
I'm sorry to keep bothering you.

192
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:46,708
The Fallen Moon really needs
you back with us, Akitsuki.

193
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:48,625
I've written a new song.

194
00:10:48,708 --> 00:10:51,625
It expresses my feelings
pretty clearly.

195
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:54,375
Please listen to it, for me.

196
00:10:55,583 --> 00:10:59,833
[YUU] The thing is, I want you
to be the one to sing it.

197
00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:16,500
[NACHI sighs]
So, it didn't work, huh?

198
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:19,375
Well, I guess we'd better
go tell the owner, then.

199
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:20,458
Wait!

200
00:11:20,541 --> 00:11:22,750
I'll go to Akitsuki's
place right now.

201
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:23,958
Huh?

202
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:25,500
[SARA]
Mm?

203
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:28,416
[YUU] Please, give me
one more chance.

204
00:11:30,625 --> 00:11:32,250
Wha--?

205
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:33,250
I think he should go.

206
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:34,500
Wait a minute, here!

207
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:36,000
[YUU] I swear to you,
I'll bring her back

208
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:38,625
by the time it's
our turn to play!

209
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:40,833
I guess it's our only choice.

210
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:41,916
Get going!

211
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,125
Okay. Thanks a lot, Nachi.

212
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:47,208
Look, from the moment I decided
to come back to this band,

213
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:49,583
I'd made up my mind to
follow your lead in whatever

214
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:51,000
you wanted to do.

215
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:53,625
You go ahead and we'll handle
sound-check without you.

216
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:55,041
[MIKASA]
Go on, hurry up!

217
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:57,916
Not a moment to waste.

218
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,750
Thanks, you guys!

219
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:11,250
[YUU panting]

220
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,333
Oh, gosh. You just missed her.

221
00:12:18,416 --> 00:12:19,333
[YUU]
Really?

222
00:12:19,416 --> 00:12:21,708
Was she going to work?

223
00:12:21,791 --> 00:12:24,958
Earlier, she said
she was off today.

224
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:26,625
[YUU]
Akitsuki.

225
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:28,125
Where are you?

226
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:36,458
[YUU gasping]

227
00:12:38,416 --> 00:12:40,041
[inaudible]

228
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:43,375
[YUU]
Could she be...?

229
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:51,125
[YUU panting]

230
00:13:04,958 --> 00:13:06,375
Oh, man!

231
00:13:06,458 --> 00:13:08,000
I was right!

232
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:11,541
[YUU]
Akitsuki!

233
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,041
What are you doing?

234
00:13:16,125 --> 00:13:18,333
Here you are. Finally.

235
00:13:18,416 --> 00:13:21,125
Shouldn't you be at your gig?
You're gonna miss it!

236
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:24,000
The band can't play
that gig without you!

237
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:26,000
I can't come back. Not now.

238
00:13:26,083 --> 00:13:27,166
Tell me why not!

239
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:30,875
[FUUKA]
I messed it all up! That's why!

240
00:13:30,958 --> 00:13:34,583
It was such a selfish
decision to leave the band.

241
00:13:34,666 --> 00:13:37,125
I know the others must be angry.

242
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,375
[YUU]
That's not true.

243
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:40,125
Come on, it has to be!

244
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,083
[gasps]

245
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:48,875
Akitsuki, I want you to
know how I really feel,

246
00:13:48,958 --> 00:13:51,916
so please, hear me out, okay?

247
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,875
I finally realize

248
00:13:54,958 --> 00:13:56,750
the things that are
most important to me

249
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:58,750
in the whole world.

250
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,791
Being devoted to something.

251
00:14:00,875 --> 00:14:03,166
My music, the band.

252
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,916
You're the one who
gave me all of that.

253
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,750
